<p>Calvin Coolidge, the 30th president of the United States, was born on 7/4/1872, in Plymouth, Vermont. He was 51 when he took office on 8/2/1923. Member: Republican Party.

	
		He left office on 3/4/1929.
	

	His occupation before the presidency: Lawyer.
	His college: Amherst.

	
		He died in Northampton, Massachusetts, on 1/5/1933.
	
</p>

